                    <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract" resp="http://syriaca.org" corresp="http://syriaca.org/persons http://syriaca.org/q http://syriaca.org/saints">Behnām and his
                        sister <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2063">Sara</persName> were
                        high-born Christian martyrs who were the children of Sennacherib. They
                        converted to Christianity through a monk, Mattai, and were killed by their
                        father. Their father later repented and became a Christian and with his wife
                        Queen Shirin. Sennacherib and Shirin built monasteries for Mar Mattai and
                        Abraham near <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/139">Mosul</placeName>.</note>
